title: 'Great Indian festival scam'
body: 'I bought this on great indian festival sale. The product specifications says it has the transfer speed upto 150mb/s. When I got the product the first thing I did was test this by copying a file to the pendrive. I barely got 22 - 25 mb/s speed(note : I inserted the drive into type B compatible port). I first thought it might be some problem with my other drive
column5: then I tested the pendrive using the most commonly used software CrystalDiskMark
column6: really shocked by the results(check the attached image). I cannot see any review with the issue I mentioned
column7: I don\'t know if others didn\'t face this issue or they are not aware of this. Is this clearance sale/defective product sale/festival sale. I have asked for return and replace unfortunately they will not give the return and refund as per their "policy". I will update about the return and replace service and the product which I get as replacement soon.'
